proximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Einion ap Ednyfed was born in Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Wales as the son of Ednyfed ap Gronwy. He had at least 1 son with Gwenllian ferch Rhys."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1298–Male":"1298–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1269–Male":"1269–Surnud","1269":"1269","1298":"1298","about 1269":"umbes 1269","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, England","Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Wales":"Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Wales"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1298–Male":"1298–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1269–Male":"1269–Kuollut","1269":"1269","1298":"1298","about 1269":"noin 1269","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, England","Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Wales":"Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Wales"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1298–Male":"1298–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1269–Male":"1269–Décédé","1269":"1269","1298":"1298","about 1269":"environ 1269","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Angleterre","Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Wales":"Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Einion ap Ednyfed est né à Hendregyda, Denbighshire, Galles, fils d’Ednyfed ap Gronwy. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Gwenllian ferch Rhys."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1298–Male":"1298–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1269–Male":"1269–V